  "notes": "Pontic Greek (Ποντιακά), archaic Greek dialect originally spoken along the Black Sea (Pontic) coast of Anatolia. Now spoken mainly in Greece. Retains many features of Ancient and Medieval Greek lost in standard Modern Greek. Uses standard Greek orthography. /i/ represented by η, ι, υ, ει, οι.",
